FBIS4-46123 "jptot022__l94032" JPRS-TOT-94-022-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 21 May 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA REGIONAL AFFAIRS IDF Seizes `Terrorist' Leader al-Dirani; Hizballah Reaction IDF Seizes `Terrorist' Leader al-Dirani; Hizballah Reaction Arad Said `Sold' to IRGC NC2105085894 Kafr Killa Voice of the South in Arabic 0830 GMT 21 May 94 NC2105085894 Kafr Killa Voice of the South Arabic BFN [Text] Our political correspondent reports that Mustafa al-Dirani sold Israeli navigator Ron Arad to the Iranian Revolutionary Guards for $300,000 in 1989. REUTER cites Husayn al-Musawi [Islamic Amal Movement leader] as saying that the abduction of al-Haj Mustafa al-Dirani will not make them deviate from the course of struggle against the Israeli enemy.
